 game situations have always been for guilds, PoP didn't change anything there. What it did change was the proportion of the zones in the expansion that were geared towards raiding. But PoP isn't dead for the soloing necro, zone into any of the usual xp zones and chances are you'll see a necro or two soloing somewhere or other. There will however probably be less incentive for soloing necros to bother getting past level 63, focusing on AA instead. That's because of the completely f-ed up situation with the 63+ spells, ie VI's mentality that only raid-oriented spellcasters need their level 63+ spells or that they should put ever more money into the banks of the uberguilds by buying those spells at ridiculous prices. FP showed that rare spells do not trickle down, no matter how many more mob drop tables it gets added to. Rare is rare and all it does is turn necros into cash farming lunatics to even have a chance of buying the spells only to end up in a bidding war that gives certain guilds more money than they'll ever need.<br /><br />Tenaiya Soulscorcher</span></font></td>
