ill level 60 mobs were giving 120% of the exp they used to give. The problem? I can think of one zone where you might find level 60 exp mobs in the old world (cazic, feel free to name others though). seb juggs are still nice, but you cant beat getting 6% aaexp for a mob that takes me roughly 3 minutes to kill (hail, a diseased underbulk).<br /><br />The flag system-<br />In theory, i think it is great. killing a mob and getting a whole raid force flagged..its sorta emp-like without the annoying shards. however, there are problems. UberguildA gets all the way to potime, before they need to recruit 25 more people to finish it off/start farming. well, they now have serveral months of raids to do to get these people flagged up, not to mention competeing with other guilds for mobs. VI is showing some thought in putting alternate quest routes, but that surely needs tweaks, we shall see how it plays out.<br /><br /><b>in closing</b>:<br />during my first few days at underbulks in pod, i was dieing on average twice per kill. kill a bulk, kill a bulk, die 3 or 4 times. I was learning pathing, how they react, where they warp, how they like their eggs in the morning, etc. I got very very very discouraged, but I kept coming back. I found my spot, and now i can solo forever, and the only time i die is when a defiler lands fear and i run into the rest of the bulks. (yes, it lands often with 180mr). <br /><br />The point? Christ guys, the expansion has been out for like two months. Cut VI some slack. They are as much in the dark as to how it will play out as we will. Dont be suprised if you see HUGE changes in the future. Give it time, I dont think VI has failed us yet, and i dont think they will this time. Dont go deleting your necros just yet (unless you are on torv, in which case, please re-roll as a paladin)<br /><br />p.s - if you think they failed us, feel free to delete yourself and not bitch.<br /><br /><br /><br />Erollia Darkrose<br />62 warlock<br />Torvonololioulious</